## 4. Implementation Phases

### Phase 1: Visual Database + Deep Filters (Day 1)
**Estimated time: 8-12 hours**

#### Step 1.1: Schema Migration
- Extend `courses` table with all new fields (backward-compatible, all optional)
- Add `collections`, `aiJobs`, `generatedContent` tables
- Add new indexes and search indexes

#### Step 1.2: Google Sheet Full Sync
- Read all 13 tabs from WSO Google Sheet
- Normalize column headers across tabs (they vary)
- Upsert into Convex (match on courseName to avoid duplicates)
- Populate: salesCopy from "Full Page Content Text", sheetTab, courseType

#### Step 1.3: Auto-Screenshot Pipeline
- For each course with a salesPage URL:
  - Use Viktor browser tool to capture full-page screenshot
  - Upload to Convex file storage
  - Store `thumbnailStorageId` and generate `thumbnailUrl`
- Run in batches of 10 to avoid rate limits
- Target: 431 screenshots (skip courses without salesPage)

#### Step 1.4: AI Categorization + Tagging
- Categories (23 types):
  ```
  AI & Automation, Paid Advertising, Social Media Marketing,
  Content Creation, SEO & Organic, Email Marketing, 
  Ecommerce & DTC, Affiliate Marketing, Agency & Consulting,
  Coaching & Courses, SaaS & Software, Real Estate,
  Finance & Investing, Copywriting & Sales, Funnel Building,
  Community Building, Personal Branding, Mindset & Productivity,
  Freelancing, Design & Creative, Health & Fitness,
  B2B & Enterprise, General Business
  ```
- AI reads: courseName + title + description + salesCopy (if available)
- Outputs: category, subcategory, tags[], difficulty, courseType, aiSummary

#### Step 1.5: Visual Directory Page
- Responsive card grid (1/2/3/4 columns)
- Card: thumbnail image, title, creator, category badge, price, tags (first 3)
- Hover: show AI summary
- Click: open course detail page
- Top bar: search, category dropdown, bundle selector, tag filter, sort (A-Z, price, rating)
- View toggle: grid / list / compact

#### Step 1.6: PowerTable Page
- Full data table with ALL columns visible
- Column sorting (click header)
- Multi-column filter panel (sidebar)
- Group-by selector: bundle, category, creator, courseType, difficulty
- Bulk select + add to collection
- Inline editing for notes, rating, status
- Export CSV

#### Step 1.7: Course Detail Page
- Hero: sales page screenshot (large), thumbnail
- Metadata panel: all fields
- Sales page iframe preview (embedded)
- File tree (if MEGA/Drive indexed)
- AI Summary + Content DNA
- Related courses (same category/creator)
- Quick actions: add to collection, rate, generate content

#### Step 1.8: Collections Page
- Create/edit/delete collections
- Color-coded collection cards
- Drag courses between collections
- Smart collections (auto-populate by filter rules)
- Mix-and-match: select courses from any bundle

### Phase 2: AI Intelligence Backend (Day 2)
**Estimated time: 6-10 hours**

#### Step 2.1: Course File Indexer
- For courses with MEGA/Drive links, scan folder structure
- Store file tree: folder names, file names, sizes, types
- Flag: hasVideo, hasPdf, hasAudio, fileCount
- Don't download files — just index metadata

#### Step 2.2: PDF Ingestion Pipeline
- For courses with PDF files in accessible folders
- Download, convert to markdown
- Store extracted text for search

#### Step 2.3: Content DNA Engine
- For each course, AI generates structured content fingerprint:
  ```json
  {
    "topics": ["facebook ads", "scaling", "creative testing"],
    "skills": ["media buying", "audience building", "analytics"],
    "tools": ["Facebook Ads Manager", "Google Analytics", "Canva"],
    "outcomes": ["scale to $1M/mo", "reduce CPA by 50%"],
    "monetizationModel": "paid course + coaching",
    "targetAudience": "ecommerce store owners",
    "uniqueAngle": "data-driven creative testing methodology"
  }
  ```

#### Step 2.4: AI Content Generator
- Select course(s) → generate:
  - Lead magnet (PDF outline, 7-day email challenge, checklist)
  - Email sequence (5-email welcome, cart abandon, webinar invite)
  - Social posts (10 posts across platforms)
  - Landing page copy (headline, subheads, bullets, CTA)
  - Blog post (2,000 word article from course concepts)
- Uses course content DNA + sales copy as source material

#### Step 2.5: Natural Language Search
- Vector embeddings for all courses (description + salesCopy + contentDNA)
- Semantic search: "find courses about scaling Facebook ads for beginners"
- Result ranking: relevance + quality score + file availability

### Phase 3: Multimedia Intelligence (Day 3)
**Estimated time: 8-12 hours**

#### Step 3.1: Video Understanding via Gemini 3 Pro
- For courses with video files:
  - Extract key frames or send video to Gemini
  - Generate: chapter summaries, key takeaways, mentioned tools, action items
  - Store as enhanced content DNA

#### Step 3.2: Audio Transcription
- Whisper API for video-to-text
- Full transcripts stored and indexed

#### Step 3.3: Cross-Course Knowledge Graph
- Map relationships between courses:
  - Same topics → "complementary courses"
  - Same creator → "creator catalog"
  - Progressive difficulty → "learning path"
  - Overlapping tools → "tool ecosystem"

