## 7. Codex Instructions

### For Codex Agent / GitHub Copilot Workspace:

**Priority order:**
1. `convex/schema.ts` — Extend schema (backward compatible, all new fields optional)
2. `convex/courses.ts` — Add paginated queries, advanced filters, batch updates
3. `convex/collections.ts` — Full CRUD for collections
4. `convex/aiJobs.ts` — Job tracking
5. `convex/generatedContent.ts` — Content storage
6. `src/pages/DirectoryPage.tsx` — Visual card grid (main deliverable)
7. `src/pages/PowerTablePage.tsx` — Advanced table
8. `src/pages/CourseDetailPage.tsx` — Full detail view
9. `src/pages/CollectionsPage.tsx` — Collections management
10. `src/pages/AIStudioPage.tsx` — AI content studio
11. `src/pages/AnalyticsPage.tsx` — Analytics dashboard
12. `src/pages/DashboardPage.tsx` — Update with real KPIs
13. `src/App.tsx` — Add routes + sidebar nav items

**Design system:**
- Dark theme (slate-950 background, consistent with existing)
- Indigo/purple accent colors
- Glass morphism cards (backdrop-blur, border-white/5)
- shadcn/ui components exclusively
- Responsive: mobile-first, 1-4 column grids
- Smooth transitions (hover, active states)

**Key constraints:**
- ALL new schema fields must be `v.optional()` for backward compatibility
- Existing data must not be lost or corrupted
- Search indexes can have max 16 filter fields
- Convex mutations are limited to 8MB per transaction
- Batch operations must chunk (max ~100 per mutation call)
- All new pages behind auth (ProtectedRoute)

