## 8. Data Sync Protocol

### Google Sheet → Convex (One-way sync, Sheet is source of truth for initial load)

```
1. Read all 13 tabs from Sheet ID: 1d1i52mxGF8dzusw_9bc2uIvJrLrrCJ1JBAWbk8ouvSM
2. Normalize headers across tabs (they vary)
3. For each row:
   a. Match to existing course by courseName (fuzzy match)
   b. If match: update empty fields only (don't overwrite existing data)
   c. If no match: insert new course
4. Set sheetTab = tab name, syncedFromSheet = true
5. After sync: update bundle courseCount
```

### Convex → Google Sheet (Bi-directional future state)
- New "Directory Sync" worksheet added to existing Sheet
- Updated after each enrichment batch
- Fields: all core + category, tags, aiSummary, status, rating

---

## 9. AI Enrichment Pipeline

```
For each course (batch of 20):
  1. Gather: courseName + title + description + salesCopy + price
  2. Call AI (via Viktor Tool Gateway):
     Prompt: "Classify this course..."
     Output: { category, subcategory, tags[], courseType, difficulty, format, aiSummary }
  3. Update course in Convex
  4. Update aiJob progress
  5. Rate limit: 2 second delay between batches
```

---

## 10. Screenshot Pipeline

```
For each course with salesPage URL:
  1. Navigate to salesPage with browser tool
  2. Wait for page load (3 second timeout)
  3. Capture viewport screenshot (1280x800)
  4. Upload to Convex file storage
  5. Set thumbnailStorageId + generate thumbnailUrl
  6. Rate limit: 1 screenshot per 2 seconds
  7. Skip: broken URLs, timeouts, NSFW warnings
```

---

## 11. Success Criteria

- [ ] All 433+ courses visible in visual card grid
- [ ] Every course has a thumbnail (screenshot or placeholder)
- [ ] Every course is categorized (23 categories)
- [ ] Every course has 3-8 tags
- [ ] Filter by: bundle, category, creator, tags, price, courseType, difficulty
- [ ] Sort by: name, price, creator, category, rating, dateAdded
- [ ] Group by: bundle, category, creator, courseType
- [ ] Search: full-text search across name, description, salesCopy
- [ ] Collections: create, edit, add/remove courses, view
- [ ] Detail page: shows all data + embedded sales page preview
- [ ] Google Sheet stays in sync
- [ ] AI Studio: generate at least 3 content types from course data
- [ ] Mobile responsive (all pages)
- [ ] Page load < 2 seconds (with lazy loading)

